Sentencas: This study deals with the electrochemical performance of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on perovskite-type materials: BaIn0.3Ti0.7O2.85 (BIT07) as electrolyte, BIT07-Ni as a cermet anode and La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) as cathode.
Titulo: Characteristics and performance improvement of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells based on BaIn0.3Ti0.7O2.85 (BIT07) as electrolyte, BIT07-Ni as anode and La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (LSCF) as cathode

Sentencas: Anode/electrolyte assemblies have been realised by tape casting and co-firing and the cathode has been deposited by screen-printing.
Titulo: Characteristics and performance improvement of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells based on BaIn0.3Ti0.7O2.85 (BIT07) as electrolyte, BIT07-Ni as anode and La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (LSCF) as cathode

Sentencas: The performance of BIT07-Ni/BIT07/LSCF cells has been determined at 700 degrees C under humidified (3% H2O) hydrogen as fuel and air as oxidant.
Titulo: Characteristics and performance improvement of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells based on BaIn0.3Ti0.7O2.85 (BIT07) as electrolyte, BIT07-Ni as anode and La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (LSCF) as cathode

Sentencas: Two cells, with different electrolyte thicknesses: 23 and 11 mu m. have been tested and they exhibited power densities at 0.7V around 209 and 336 mW cm(-2), respectively.
Titulo: Characteristics and performance improvement of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells based on BaIn0.3Ti0.7O2.85 (BIT07) as electrolyte, BIT07-Ni as anode and La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (LSCF) as cathode

Sentencas: Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy (EIS) measurements have also been carried out and allowed to differentiate between the series and polarisation resistances.
Titulo: Characteristics and performance improvement of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells based on BaIn0.3Ti0.7O2.85 (BIT07) as electrolyte, BIT07-Ni as anode and La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ (LSCF) as cathode
